# .privacy-denylist.example
#
# Copy to `.privacy-denylist.local` (which is gitignored) and fill in the
# exact strings that must never appear in this public repository.
#
# One case-insensitive literal per line. Blank lines and #-comments ignored.
# The pre-commit privacy gate matches these against staged content and
# reports only the rule number — never the matched value.
#
# `make privacy-init` generates a starter file automatically.
#
# Typical entries:
#
#   Your Full Legal Name
#   you@example.com
#   ABCDE12345            (Apple Developer Team ID)
#   your-macos-username
#   00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000   (provider account UUID)
